\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\i\f0\fs28  Java source files always have  Package and Import statements at its beginning lines.The first non-comment line of  Java source files is a package statement. After that,import statements can follow.\i0\f1\fs22\par

\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\i\f0\fs28 after the package has been specified programmer can  also brief the description of the purpose of the program by commenting it.\i0\f1\fs22\par

