Comments.\par

\pard{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf4\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\ulnone\i comments are of implementation and documenttion comments.\ul\i0\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\i Implementation Comment Formats \ulnone inludes the below.\ul\i0\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\ulnone\i Comments mainly used to give overview of code.\ul\i0\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\i Single-Line Comments \ulnone\b : \b0 It includes Short comments can appear on a single line indented to the level of the code using \b\fs32 /* \b0\fs28 and  \b\fs32 */\ul\b0\i0\fs28\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\ulnone\i  If a comment can\rquote t be written in a single line, it should follow the block comment format .\ul\i0\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\ulnone\i  \ul Block comments \ulnone can start with  \b\fs44 /*\fs36  \b0\fs28 and  ends with \b\fs44 */ \b0\fs28 This can be done by selecting a part of the code to be commented and using shortcut as \b\fs32 ctrl,shift,/ \b0\fs28 and same way decmmenting can be done by using the shortcut as \b\fs32 ctrl,shift,\\\ul\i0\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\b0\i\fs28 End-Of-Line Comments \ulnone begins with  \b\fs36 // \b0\fs28 comment delimiter.\ul\b\i0\fs32\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\b0\i\fs28 Documentation Comments\b\fs36 :\ulnone\b0\fs28 Doc comments describe Java classes, interfaces, constructors, methods, and fields. Each doc comment is set inside the comment delimiters  as \b\fs36 /**...*/\ul\i0\fs28\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\ulnone\b0\i Doc comments should not be positioned inside a method or constructor definition block.\ul\b\i0\par
{\pntext\f4\'B7\tab}\ulnone\b0\i  use an implementation block comment  to give information about a class, interface, variable, or method .\ul\b\i0\par

